<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1950,1976]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityName="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[332,847,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hubeiensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[332,572,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Maladera hubeiensis</emphasis>
Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[862,925,1951,1977]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the similar 
<taxonomicName authority="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityName="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yipinglangensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1219,1436,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">M. yipinglangensis</emphasis>
Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[421,483,1987,2013]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having the dorsolateral apical process of the phallobase straight apically and the apical portion (1/7 of entire paramere length) of the fused left and right parameres being always triangular, as well as having the basal group of setae of the metatibia positioned at the middle instead of being well behind middle as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[180,393,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yipinglangensis">
<emphasis box="[180,393,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">M. yipinglangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
